Types of waits in selenium

1. Implicitly wait
	The Implicit Wait in Selenium is used to tell the web driver 
	to wait for a certain amount of time before it throws a No Such Element Exception.
	
	syntax: driver.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(TimeOut, TimeUnit.SECONDS); \
		The duration may be in seconds or milliseconds etc.
		
2. Explicitly wait
	The Explicit Wait in Selenium is used to tell the Web Driver to wait for certain 
	conditions to be true before throwing “ElementNotVisibleException” exception.
	
	syntax:
		WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(WebDriverRefrence,TimeOut);